Class Master

java.lang.Object
Master
public class Master extends Object
Main root solver class which runs the terminal interface for testing the multithreaded root finder and handles creating/destroying the threads.
See Also:
RootFinder

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main​(String[] args)
      Main method for running the command line interface for selecting which test you would like to run. Options 1 or 2 are displayed to the user, and response is prompted.
      Parameters:
      args - input args for method

    • largeTest

      public static void largeTest()
      Performs a large root solving test with 3000 3-tuples to be computed, distributed over 10 threads. Once all roots are computed the number of roots sets each thread computed is displayed.
      See Also:
      RootData, CircularBuffer, ExecutorService

    • smallTest

      public static void smallTest()
      Performs a small test for the root finder by running 30 3-tuples through the RootFinder class with workload distributed over 10 threads. Computed roots are simultaneously outputed after computed with the thread that computed them also displayed.
      See Also:
      RootFinder, CircularBuffer, ExecutorService
